Do a case-insensitive search for "demo2s" in a string:

Copy
let str = "Visit Demo2s.com";
let patt1 = /demo2s/i;
let result = str.match(patt1);
console.log(result);
Output:


Description
The i modifier can do case-insensitive matching.

Use the ignoreCase property to check whether or not the "i" modifier is set.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
i	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Copy
new RegExp("regexp", "i") or simply: /regexp/i
